psxamiga.library/PSXExecute                       psxamiga.library/PSXExecute

    NAME
	PSXExecute -- Start the program that EPC currently points to.

    SYNOPSIS
	result = PSXExecute()
        D0.l     

        LONG     PSXExecute()

    FUNCTION
        Let the Yaroze terminal jump to the address that the EPC (Program
        Counter) currently points to. Make sure you set the EPC using the
        SetCPUReg function before calling this function!

    RESULTS
       result      = Succes/Failure indicator. If the function succeeded,
                     then this will be ULONG zero, otherwise it is the
                     IO_ERROR field from the IORequest.

    NOTES
        Currently supported development systems are: YAROZE

        During the execution of the program all other function calls are
        not possible because the Yaroze Terminal will go offline.

    SEE ALSO
        include/psxamiga.i, exec/io.i

